PARAMETERS (TO SPECIFY WHERE TO DEPLOY BUILD)
1) TYPES
	• Choice parameter: When you have multiple options we can select one.
STEPS:
		1. Create a CI Job — After the .war file is generated.
		2. click on Configure
		3. Select This project is Parameterized > Add parameter
		4. name : environment
		5. choice : dev, test, uat, Prod
		6. Save
So If you click on build now you can specify the environment where you are deploying the build.
	• 2) String Parameter: To pass multiple inputs
		○ Sample name: env or client
		○ Save
		○ Build with Parameter: You can then type multiple inputs like Prod, client 3
	• 3) Multi line string: To pass input on multiple lines. Select multi-line string -> Save. You can write input on multiple lines.
	• 4) Boolean : True or False (To keep backup of a build)
	• 5) File : To build files — To upload files from local computer.

TO CHANGE JENKINS DEFAULT PORT NUMBER FROM 8080 TO 8090

	1. Vim /usr/lib/systemd/system/jenkins.service
	2. esc
	3. :67 (Go to line number)
	4. Modify the port number to your choice
	5. Save
	6. Systemctl daemon-reload
	7. Systemctl restart jenkins.service
	8. Systemctl status jenkins.service
	9. Go to browser -> localhost:NewPort

PASSWORDLESS LOGIN: (IN Case u forget Jenkins Password)

	1. Vim /var/lib/jenkins/config.xml
	2. escape
	3. :7 (Go to line 7)
	4. Replace true with false (Security brace)
	5. Restart Jenkins
	6. check status

CHANGING BUILD LIMITS FROM DEFAULT 2 TO YOUR NUMBER CHOICE.
Dashboard -> Manage Jenkins -> nodes -> built-in node -> Configure -> number of executors -> 3 -> save.

NOTE: TROUBLESHOOTING SCENARIOS
What this means is the number of builds at a time, if its 5 or more, Jenkins might crash. To resolve, restart EC2 instance, once you restart IP changes.
TO RESOLVE:
Restart the Service
	• systemctl restart jenkins.service
	• systemctl status jenkins.service
Then you will be able to access Jenkins dashboard.

TO BE ABLE TO RESTORE DELETED PROJECT
	1. Dashboard -> Manage Jenkins -> Plugins -> available plugins
	2. Search Job Configuration History -> Install -> Go back to top page
	3. On the left blade click on Job Config History
	4. — show deleted jobs only
NOTE: You must have signed in with your username and Password into Jenkins. If u use passwordless login you can't use the Job config History plugin to restore deleted Project.
	1. click on restore project
	2. select yes
	3. click Enable


